cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the problem of tracking evolving news stories across different domains/sources, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a learning-to-rank framework and uses graph-based representations, which are common in the fields of machine learning and data mining, suggesting that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
